  "about": [
    "Zazaa Ganbold is a Mongolian born contemporary artist working across Germany, Portugal and Mongolia. Her multidisciplinary practice spans painting, collage, digital media and textile based works. Her work investigates the relationship between the visible and the invisible, the material and the spiritual, and the continuous transformation of human consciousness.",
    "Rather than treating the human body as a representational subject, Ganbold approaches it as a living vessel of memory, emotion and symbolic knowledge. Figures dissolve into animals, plants, masks and archetypal forms, creating visual landscapes in which personal experience intersects with collective memory and cultural imagination.",
    "Rooted in Mongolian cosmology and nomadic ideas of interconnectedness, while informed by European contemporary art and psychological thought, her work transforms cultural references into an open symbolic language. Dreams, intuition and mythology become ways of understanding reality beyond what can be rationally explained."
  ],
  "contactText": "For inquiries regarding artworks, exhibitions, commissions or collaborations, please get in touch.",
